<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Cusset, Fl. Cameroun 30: 64" authorityYear="1987" baseAuthorityName="Engl." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Macropodiella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Macropodiella pellucida" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pellucida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Macropodiella pellucida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed on http://www.iucnredlist.org as Endangered (
<bibRefCitation author="Ghogue, J-P" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B43" refString="Ghogue, J-P, 2010o. Macropodiellapellucida. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T45904A11021892. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Macropodiellapellucida. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 45904 A 11021892. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2010 o">Ghogue 2010o</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Onana, JM" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B66" refString="Onana, JM, Cheek, M, 2011. Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments." year="2011">Onana and Cheek (2011)</bibRefCitation>
maintained the Endangered status of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ghogue, J-P" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B43" refString="Ghogue, J-P, 2010o. Macropodiellapellucida. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T45904A11021892. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Macropodiellapellucida. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 45904 A 11021892. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2010 o">Ghogue (2010o)</bibRefCitation>
. The taxon is endemic to Cameroon and known from two localities. The extent of occurrence is less than 4 km2 and the area of occupancy of this species is estimated at less than 20 km2. There have not been further threats at the habitat of the species since the previous assessment. The species is reassessed as Endangered, maintaining the previous status. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Endangered ENB2ab (iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
